WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:09.843 --> 00:00:12.046
♪ dramatic music ♪

2
00:00:18.952 --> 00:00:20.554
[gunfire]

3
00:00:24.425 --> 00:00:26.194
[Calvin]
Where's the rest of the team?

4
00:00:26.294 --> 00:00:28.596
- [machine gun firing]
- That's Roner's pig barking.

5
00:00:28.696 --> 00:00:29.997
We got to get him and beat feet.

6
00:00:30.098 --> 00:00:31.599
Come on. On me. let's go.

7
00:00:33.534 --> 00:00:35.436
[cell phone ringing]

8
00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:43.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

9
00:00:47.881 --> 00:00:48.881
Monica.

10
00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:50.618
Monica?

11
00:00:51.419 --> 00:00:52.920
Monica. where are you?

12
00:00:53.987 --> 00:00:56.124
Monica? Monica!

13
00:00:56.224 --> 00:00:58.058
[gasps]

14
00:00:59.059 --> 00:01:00.994
[grunts softly]

15
00:01:08.736 --> 00:01:10.504
[owl hoots outside]

16
00:01:15.576 --> 00:01:17.245
[exhales]

17
00:01:28.122 --> 00:01:30.291
♪ gentle music ♪

18
00:01:41.369 --> 00:01:42.970
[lowing]

19
00:01:43.271 --> 00:01:45.439
♪

20
00:02:04.925 --> 00:02:07.660
[lowing]

21
00:02:07.661 --> 00:02:09.563
[clicks tongue]

22
00:02:11.699 --> 00:02:13.467
Better get moving...

23
00:02:14.802 --> 00:02:16.136
...or figure out
how cruel this life is.

24
00:02:16.404 --> 00:02:18.572
♪

25
00:02:33.321 --> 00:02:35.523
♪

26
00:03:00.281 --> 00:03:02.416
♪

27
00:03:08.556 --> 00:03:10.758
I'm late. Again.

28
00:03:10.858 --> 00:03:12.359
[Kayce]
Corral needs safeguarding.

29
00:03:12.360 --> 00:03:13.893
You dial that in after school.

30
00:03:13.894 --> 00:03:15.863
[Tate]
Corral's got to wait.

31
00:03:15.963 --> 00:03:18.398
I'm sleeping over at Deebo's
after the rez meeting.

32
00:03:18.399 --> 00:03:19.366
What meeting?

33
00:03:19.367 --> 00:03:21.201
For the protest

34
00:03:21.302 --> 00:03:24.071
against the mine that'll
dump toxins onto Broken Rock.

35
00:03:24.171 --> 00:03:25.706
Running this ranch is our fight.

36
00:03:25.806 --> 00:03:27.275
I got to go.

37
00:03:27.375 --> 00:03:29.977
What about your breakfast?

38
00:03:35.816 --> 00:03:38.452
Tate. hold up.

39
00:03:44.492 --> 00:03:47.395
Look. I know
your mom was better at all this.

40
00:03:47.528 --> 00:03:49.430
[car approaching]

41
00:03:57.738 --> 00:03:59.307
You know this is rez land.

42
00:04:00.173 --> 00:04:01.275
Technically.

43
00:04:01.409 --> 00:04:02.742
U.S. Marshal
has no jurisdiction here.

44
00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:04.077
[Calvin]
Good.

45
00:04:04.177 --> 00:04:05.244
'cause. technically.
what I'm doing for you

46
00:04:05.245 --> 00:04:07.047
is illegal as hell.

47
00:04:08.416 --> 00:04:09.750
I got shot. fragged

48
00:04:09.850 --> 00:04:11.352
and nearly court-martialed
'cause of you.

49
00:04:11.452 --> 00:04:13.053
Consider us even.

50
00:04:13.153 --> 00:04:14.154
[Calvin]
You gonna let him speak to his

51
00:04:14.254 --> 00:04:15.423
old team leader like that. Tate?

52
00:04:15.523 --> 00:04:16.857
[Tate] Man's got
a problem with authority.

53
00:04:16.957 --> 00:04:19.092
Show him a good time. Cal.
He needs it.

54
00:04:19.192 --> 00:04:20.594
[Calvin] Two frogmen
with enough explosives

55
00:04:20.694 --> 00:04:22.429
to flatten the Rockies?

56
00:04:22.430 --> 00:04:24.798
Not even your old man
can spoil that fun.

57
00:04:27.601 --> 00:04:29.837
Looks like
you got pigeon tossed.

58
00:04:30.604 --> 00:04:32.205
Take some R&R. man.

59
00:04:32.306 --> 00:04:33.641
No days off on the ranch.

60
00:04:33.741 --> 00:04:37.445
[chuckles] From
kicking doors to baling hay.

61
00:04:37.545 --> 00:04:39.780
- So much for "evolve or die."
- [vehicle engine starts]

62
00:04:39.913 --> 00:04:41.248
It's hard to believe
you couldn't hold down

63
00:04:41.349 --> 00:04:42.650
- any of your marriages.
- [whistles]

64
00:04:42.750 --> 00:04:44.318
Still going
for the jugular. I see.

65
00:04:44.418 --> 00:04:45.986
Don't make me put you
in your place. sailor.

66
00:04:46.119 --> 00:04:47.988
How much I owe you for these?

67
00:04:48.088 --> 00:04:49.923
Compliments of the meth head
I took 'em off of.

68
00:04:50.023 --> 00:04:53.394
But you mind sharing
what you're fixing to blow up?

69
00:04:53.494 --> 00:04:55.596
This a wellness check?

70
00:04:56.464 --> 00:04:58.265
All the shrapnel you've taken.

71
00:04:58.366 --> 00:05:00.734
it's more like a "no man
left behind" kind of thing.

72
00:05:01.602 --> 00:05:03.871
Okay. well. if you insist
on "swim buddying" me.

73
00:05:03.971 --> 00:05:05.806
I'm gonna put you to work.

74
00:05:05.906 --> 00:05:08.341
♪ quiet music ♪

75
00:05:08.342 --> 00:05:10.611
[Calvin] I moved here three
months ago to start this team.

76
00:05:10.711 --> 00:05:13.012
and I-I still don't get
this way of life.

77
00:05:13.013 --> 00:05:15.816
Really. what do you do
out here all day?

78
00:05:16.817 --> 00:05:18.586
Work the land. tend the herd.

79
00:05:18.686 --> 00:05:19.986
Ranching's in my blood.

80
00:05:19.987 --> 00:05:21.955
[Calvin]
All those years of door-kicking.

81
00:05:22.055 --> 00:05:26.025
you never once mentioned that
you're some Montana Rockefeller.

82
00:05:26.026 --> 00:05:28.362
That was the best part
about being a SEAL.

83
00:05:29.530 --> 00:05:31.699
Yeah. Dutton didn't matter
in the Teams.

84
00:05:31.999 --> 00:05:34.167
♪

85
00:05:40.708 --> 00:05:42.410
- [chuckles]
- [laughs]

86
00:05:43.176 --> 00:05:45.012
Better shot now
than when we were teammates.

87
00:05:45.112 --> 00:05:46.879
Yeah. well. I need to be.

88
00:05:46.880 --> 00:05:49.082
Marshal team's a tactical
Swiss Army knife.

89
00:05:49.182 --> 00:05:50.384
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

90
00:05:50.518 --> 00:05:52.686
- Crushing a lot of skulls?
- Oh. yeah. Gangs

91
00:05:52.786 --> 00:05:54.822
and cartels. race warriors.

92
00:05:54.922 --> 00:05:56.289
It may look like God's country.

93
00:05:56.390 --> 00:05:57.891
but devil's running free
out here.

94
00:05:57.991 --> 00:05:59.593
[Kayce] That's why
I'm at peace on this ranch.

95
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:02.396
Oh. yeah. Frogman at peace.
that's a notion.

96
00:06:02.496 --> 00:06:04.865
Just tell me
you don't see ghosts.

97
00:06:08.402 --> 00:06:10.036
I guess my time after the Teams

98
00:06:10.037 --> 00:06:12.072
wasn't as smooth as yours. right?

99
00:06:12.973 --> 00:06:14.542
Crushing pills
and throwing hands.

100
00:06:14.642 --> 00:06:18.178
I mean. I went full gong show
after the Navy. but...

101
00:06:18.278 --> 00:06:19.913
the marshals were my salvation.

102
00:06:20.848 --> 00:06:23.717
And I'm guessing you've got
your own demons to conquer.

103
00:06:23.817 --> 00:06:26.520
and I could sure use
another door-kicker.

104
00:06:27.287 --> 00:06:31.459
My life's been "kill
or be killed" for too long. man.

105
00:06:32.993 --> 00:06:35.629
Okay. Fair enough.

106
00:06:39.032 --> 00:06:40.534
You know.
I could use a favor. though.

107
00:06:40.634 --> 00:06:42.402
Got two fugitives.
they're holed up in the hills

108
00:06:42.503 --> 00:06:45.338
just-just east of your family's
old ranch. I can't locate 'em.

109
00:06:46.173 --> 00:06:47.574
Probably using
an old sheeper cabin

110
00:06:47.575 --> 00:06:49.042
up where I'd track bighorns
with my brothers.

111
00:06:49.142 --> 00:06:52.079
But the wildlife
and the terrain make it a no-go

112
00:06:52.179 --> 00:06:53.413
for tenderfoots like you.

113
00:06:53.514 --> 00:06:55.615
[laughs]

114
00:06:55.616 --> 00:06:57.685
Not lacking ways
to die in Montana.

115
00:06:57.785 --> 00:06:58.919
Explains a lot about you.

116
00:06:59.019 --> 00:07:00.420
- [chuckles]
- Sure would be nice

117
00:07:00.521 --> 00:07:01.889
to bag these guys. though.

118
00:07:02.923 --> 00:07:04.792
They're preying on rez women.

119
00:07:06.527 --> 00:07:08.028
I'll drive.

120
00:07:12.032 --> 00:07:13.433
[tribal officer]
<i>Mr. Chairman.</i>

121
00:07:13.534 --> 00:07:15.135
the mine announcement
is set for tomorrow.

122
00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:17.938
The Secretary of the Interior
will land at 9:30.

123
00:07:18.038 --> 00:07:19.973
deliver her remarks
at the mine location.

124
00:07:20.073 --> 00:07:22.776
then head back to Washington
at 11:00.

125
00:07:22.876 --> 00:07:24.277
Well. plundering

126
00:07:24.377 --> 00:07:27.014
and pillaging is more efficient
than it used to be.

127
00:07:27.114 --> 00:07:29.282
Government gets
cell phone magnets.

128
00:07:29.382 --> 00:07:31.619
Broken Rock gets
an even higher cancer rate.

129
00:07:31.752 --> 00:07:34.187
[council member] The rare earth
mineral site isn't on our land.

130
00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.989
- We have no recourse.
- [Mo] It's on our river.

131
00:07:36.089 --> 00:07:38.157
where our forefathers
watered their horses.

132
00:07:38.158 --> 00:07:40.928
America's policies have
long dumped a steady flow

133
00:07:41.028 --> 00:07:43.163
of poisons on our people.

134
00:07:43.296 --> 00:07:44.832
Using a literal river indicates

135
00:07:44.965 --> 00:07:46.466
they're running lower
on imagination

136
00:07:46.600 --> 00:07:48.536
than cruelty.

137
00:07:50.771 --> 00:07:52.806
[horse nickers]

138
00:07:57.778 --> 00:08:00.548
Hell no. I'm not getting
on that beast. Cal.

139
00:08:00.648 --> 00:08:02.983
You took down a Sinaloa kingpin.

140
00:08:03.083 --> 00:08:04.852
but you're afraid of horses?

141
00:08:05.853 --> 00:08:07.687
Well. this'll be fun.

142
00:08:07.688 --> 00:08:09.856
Signed up to crush skulls.
not join the rodeo. boss.

143
00:08:09.857 --> 00:08:11.158
Well. the only way
to traverse this land

144
00:08:11.291 --> 00:08:13.226
is on horseback. Kayce.

145
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:14.361
meet my marshals.

146
00:08:14.494 --> 00:08:16.829
Andrea. Miles. Belle.

147
00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:18.365
Now. listen up.

148
00:08:18.498 --> 00:08:20.834
Federal warrants are for
John King. Tyler White.

149
00:08:20.934 --> 00:08:23.604
and the route we're taking.
it is rife with grizzlies

150
00:08:23.704 --> 00:08:25.806
and rattlesnakes
and rock slides.

151
00:08:25.906 --> 00:08:27.975
so Kayce's in charge.

152
00:08:30.978 --> 00:08:33.881
Uh...
it's gonna be a rough haul.

153
00:08:34.014 --> 00:08:35.549
Biggest risk is
your horse spooking.

154
00:08:35.649 --> 00:08:36.684
You saying that thing
might buck me?

155
00:08:36.817 --> 00:08:38.418
[Belle]
If its ears work.

156
00:08:40.120 --> 00:08:41.353
Just pull the reins to stop.

157
00:08:41.354 --> 00:08:43.056
kick her in the belly to go.

158
00:08:45.292 --> 00:08:46.660
Want a boost?

159
00:08:46.760 --> 00:08:48.528
It'd be the last thing you do.

160
00:08:48.629 --> 00:08:51.064
♪ gentle music ♪

161
00:08:59.239 --> 00:09:02.374
Cal never shared he was buddies
with Kayce Dutton.

162
00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:03.877
[Andrea]
Something special about him?

163
00:09:03.977 --> 00:09:07.080
Honey. have you done any
research on your new hometown?

164
00:09:07.180 --> 00:09:10.017
[laughs]
Montana is a detour. not a home.

165
00:09:10.117 --> 00:09:11.551
[Miles] Duttons owned
the biggest ranch in Montana

166
00:09:11.652 --> 00:09:12.786
for generations.

167
00:09:12.886 --> 00:09:15.022
Kayce sold it
to my tribe last year.

168
00:09:15.122 --> 00:09:16.790
His dad was
the governor who was killed.

169
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:19.391
brother Jamie's the attorney
general who went missing.

170
00:09:19.392 --> 00:09:21.427
Does any of this ring a bell?

171
00:09:21.428 --> 00:09:23.096
No.

172
00:09:23.196 --> 00:09:24.798
but I dig his hat.

173
00:09:29.903 --> 00:09:32.605
Cabin's just beyond
that ridgeline.

174
00:09:32.606 --> 00:09:34.507
Okay. That trigger
finger getting itchy?

175
00:09:34.608 --> 00:09:37.444
[scoffs] My days of
running into fire are over.

176
00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:40.413
Okay. y'all.
Let's shake some trees.

177
00:09:40.513 --> 00:09:42.783
♪ low. propulsive music ♪

178
00:09:50.423 --> 00:09:52.092
[sighs]

179
00:09:58.231 --> 00:10:00.433
[insects trilling]

180
00:10:05.806 --> 00:10:07.975
♪

181
00:10:22.222 --> 00:10:23.456
[Andrea]
Runner!

182
00:10:30.731 --> 00:10:31.899
[Calvin]
U.S. Marshals!

183
00:10:33.166 --> 00:10:34.467
[horse snorts]

184
00:10:36.069 --> 00:10:37.304
Hyah!

185
00:10:37.404 --> 00:10:39.406
♪ tense music ♪

186
00:11:01.094 --> 00:11:03.363
♪

187
00:11:05.132 --> 00:11:06.498
[horse neighs]

188
00:11:06.499 --> 00:11:08.702
We got to get ahead of him.

189
00:11:20.347 --> 00:11:23.383
♪

190
00:11:38.065 --> 00:11:40.500
[Midland's
"Glass Half Empty" playing]

191
00:11:43.003 --> 00:11:47.474
<i>♪ No. it ain't all about
the whiskey or beer ♪</i>

192
00:11:47.574 --> 00:11:49.509
<i>♪ And you'll
understand when you... ♪</i>

193
00:11:49.609 --> 00:11:51.211
You shame me
to come out with your team.

194
00:11:51.311 --> 00:11:53.246
then you drag me
to a place like this.

195
00:11:53.380 --> 00:11:54.714
Well. Cal only picked this spot

196
00:11:54.815 --> 00:11:56.216
'cause the stockyards
don't serve liquor.

197
00:11:56.349 --> 00:11:59.418
Now. see. Belle's taste
leans more five-star

198
00:11:59.419 --> 00:12:00.587
than "dive bar."

199
00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:02.589
[Kayce] You rode
the hair off that horse.

200
00:12:02.689 --> 00:12:04.892
Are you local?
You got a familiar way to you.

201
00:12:05.025 --> 00:12:06.258
I get that a lot.

202
00:12:06.259 --> 00:12:07.427
Belle used to be ATF.

203
00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:09.428
She joined us two months ago.

204
00:12:09.429 --> 00:12:10.898
Undercover specialist.

205
00:12:10.998 --> 00:12:12.632
so holds her cards close.

206
00:12:14.201 --> 00:12:15.235
I'm okay.

207
00:12:15.368 --> 00:12:16.402
My dad told me.
"Never trust a cop

208
00:12:16.403 --> 00:12:17.437
who won't drink with you."

209
00:12:17.537 --> 00:12:19.439
Same logic applies to cowboys.

210
00:12:19.539 --> 00:12:21.074
Dad's a cop?

211
00:12:21.174 --> 00:12:23.510
You join the marshals
to impress him or defy him?

212
00:12:23.610 --> 00:12:25.578
Avenge him.
Thank you for that glimpse

213
00:12:25.712 --> 00:12:27.914
into your psych jacket.

214
00:12:27.915 --> 00:12:30.183
[La Caretilla's "Jenny" playing]

215
00:12:30.283 --> 00:12:32.619
[crowd groaning]

216
00:12:32.752 --> 00:12:34.421
[singing in Spanish]

217
00:12:36.957 --> 00:12:39.626
Our tradecraft is not
meant for hijacking jukeboxes.

218
00:12:39.759 --> 00:12:41.293
You know. it's becoming clearer

219
00:12:41.294 --> 00:12:43.897
every day why you got
kicked off your unit in D.C.

220
00:12:44.631 --> 00:12:47.567
Honey. there's three things
you don't do in Montana.

221
00:12:47.667 --> 00:12:49.036
Pet the buffalo.

222
00:12:49.136 --> 00:12:51.303
try to outdrink Canadians.

223
00:12:51.304 --> 00:12:53.272
- and mess with cowboys' music.
- [country music playing]

224
00:12:53.273 --> 00:12:55.976
[patrons cheering]

225
00:12:56.109 --> 00:12:57.945
Think that's my cue to leave.

226
00:12:58.078 --> 00:12:59.646
No. Hey. we all should.

227
00:12:59.746 --> 00:13:02.282
'cause tomorrow's mine rally
could be a powder-keg. so...

228
00:13:02.382 --> 00:13:04.116
Broken Rock will be
out in force.

229
00:13:04.117 --> 00:13:05.651
Locals. too. Could get salty.

230
00:13:05.652 --> 00:13:07.020
My kid's gonna be there.

231
00:13:08.421 --> 00:13:10.723
I can be extra eyes
and ears if you need 'em.

232
00:13:11.558 --> 00:13:13.526
One-time deal.

233
00:13:14.761 --> 00:13:15.963
[Calvin]
I'll deputize you.

234
00:13:16.096 --> 00:13:17.364
Here.

235
00:13:18.431 --> 00:13:19.499
Welcome

236
00:13:19.599 --> 00:13:21.401
to the U.S. Marshals.

237
00:13:28.608 --> 00:13:31.677
<i>[singing in Lakota]</i>

238
00:13:31.678 --> 00:13:34.647
[loud chatter]

239
00:13:36.416 --> 00:13:37.550
Haven't been this outmanned

240
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.920
since that PSD
we pulled in J-Bad.

241
00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:43.123
I see you won't be outgunned.

242
00:13:43.223 --> 00:13:44.524
Still licensed to carry that?

243
00:13:44.657 --> 00:13:47.327
Gave up my badge.
not being Montanan.

244
00:13:48.828 --> 00:13:51.698
[singing continues]

245
00:13:54.334 --> 00:13:55.735
So. what's with the pictures?

246
00:13:55.835 --> 00:13:59.139
Cancer victims from toxins
dumped onto the rez.

247
00:14:06.146 --> 00:14:07.780
Tate.

248
00:14:11.384 --> 00:14:13.053
U.S. Marshal?

249
00:14:13.153 --> 00:14:14.054
What are you doing?

250
00:14:14.187 --> 00:14:16.223
Just helping out Cal.

251
00:14:16.323 --> 00:14:18.091
- You need to go home. buddy.
- What?

252
00:14:18.191 --> 00:14:20.227
I need to be here.

253
00:14:20.327 --> 00:14:21.561
This rally could get violent.

254
00:14:21.661 --> 00:14:23.062
Since when are you
concerned about me

255
00:14:23.063 --> 00:14:24.363
being exposed to violence?

256
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:26.934
Since everything
we've been through.

257
00:14:27.034 --> 00:14:28.035
Go home.

258
00:14:28.135 --> 00:14:30.904
After how much Mom suffered?

259
00:14:31.038 --> 00:14:33.205
You should be leading
the charge here.

260
00:14:33.206 --> 00:14:35.308
not waving the white flag.

261
00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:39.779
[singing continues]

262
00:14:57.530 --> 00:14:58.431
Whoa. boss man's here.

263
00:14:58.531 --> 00:15:00.400
I'm your boss. not Gifford.

264
00:15:00.500 --> 00:15:02.268
Well. only one of you
is a presidential appointee.

265
00:15:02.269 --> 00:15:03.570
How long before
he mentions that?

266
00:15:03.670 --> 00:15:05.238
Harry. what brings
you down from Helena?

267
00:15:05.338 --> 00:15:06.940
Ah. when there's a member
of the president's

268
00:15:07.040 --> 00:15:08.675
cabinet in my state.
you bet your bottom dollar

269
00:15:08.775 --> 00:15:10.010
I'm showing up.

270
00:15:10.110 --> 00:15:11.578
You got all dolled up
for the secretary.

271
00:15:11.678 --> 00:15:13.813
Choke strap's out
of respect for the president.

272
00:15:13.913 --> 00:15:15.482
The man did appoint me.
after all.

273
00:15:15.582 --> 00:15:17.449
Cal. I want you to meet. uh.

274
00:15:17.450 --> 00:15:19.052
Secretary Clarkson's
head of. uh. security.

275
00:15:19.152 --> 00:15:20.887
This is Special Agent Dan Glenn.

276
00:15:20.988 --> 00:15:22.755
This is Director Owen Kilborn

277
00:15:22.855 --> 00:15:24.157
from Fish. Game and Parks.

278
00:15:24.257 --> 00:15:25.758
[Owen] Crowd's amped up.
Appreciate you marshals

279
00:15:25.858 --> 00:15:27.094
running point on my turf.

280
00:15:27.227 --> 00:15:28.760
Well. we're not gonna
step on your toes. so...

281
00:15:28.761 --> 00:15:29.963
No toes to step on.

282
00:15:30.063 --> 00:15:31.364
I'm the only
Fish and Game asset here.

283
00:15:31.464 --> 00:15:32.665
[Harry]
That's why I formed this team.

284
00:15:32.765 --> 00:15:34.067
Last line of defense
in the region.

285
00:15:34.167 --> 00:15:35.735
[Andrea]
I hope we live up to the hype.

286
00:15:35.835 --> 00:15:37.937
The hornet's nest is a-stirring.

287
00:15:38.071 --> 00:15:40.673
Make sure nobody kicks it.

288
00:15:42.109 --> 00:15:45.512
[singing continues]

289
00:15:48.448 --> 00:15:51.450
[Thomas]
Ah. This country's latest form

290
00:15:51.451 --> 00:15:54.486
of radioactive colonialism
might be worth it

291
00:15:54.487 --> 00:15:57.324
if it allows me to see
the reclusive Kayce Dutton.

292
00:15:57.457 --> 00:15:59.126
[chuckles]

293
00:15:59.259 --> 00:16:00.793
Thought you traded in
your badge.

294
00:16:00.893 --> 00:16:02.262
I'm just moonlighting.
I'm only here 'cause

295
00:16:02.362 --> 00:16:03.997
Tate's being a stubborn
pain in my ass.

296
00:16:04.131 --> 00:16:06.299
[Thomas] Dutton father and son
that don't see eye to eye?

297
00:16:06.399 --> 00:16:07.834
Hard to believe.

298
00:16:07.934 --> 00:16:10.637
How are things on East Camp?

299
00:16:10.770 --> 00:16:13.340
Eh. you know.
I got 5.000 acres. 300 pair.

300
00:16:13.473 --> 00:16:16.309
and a disobedient teenager.
I'm living the dream.

301
00:16:16.443 --> 00:16:17.809
[Mo chuckles]

302
00:16:17.810 --> 00:16:18.778
I don't think
we've seen you on Broken Rock

303
00:16:18.878 --> 00:16:21.114
since Monica's burial.

304
00:16:21.914 --> 00:16:23.983
Yeah. she. uh. she picked
out her favorite spot

305
00:16:24.084 --> 00:16:25.485
on East Camp
for me to visit her.

306
00:16:25.585 --> 00:16:26.853
It isn't her grave

307
00:16:26.953 --> 00:16:29.556
that keeps you connected
to her spirit.

308
00:16:30.323 --> 00:16:32.692
[Glenn] <i>Secretary's on target.
Eyes open.</i>

309
00:16:32.792 --> 00:16:34.994
[singing continues]

310
00:16:35.828 --> 00:16:38.731
- [booing]
- [indistinct shouting]

311
00:16:40.067 --> 00:16:41.701
Cal wants us patrolling
together. Dutton.

312
00:16:41.834 --> 00:16:43.370
[Thomas]
You'll like Dust Cloud.

313
00:16:43.503 --> 00:16:46.172
He's one of our best cops.
when not on probation.

314
00:16:46.173 --> 00:16:49.242
[Mo] Yeah. he'll remind you of
the mustangs you used to break.

315
00:16:50.043 --> 00:16:51.343
[Thomas]
Don't be a stranger. Kayce.

316
00:16:51.344 --> 00:16:54.214
Solitude can be dangerous.

317
00:16:54.314 --> 00:16:55.548
So can being a Dutton.

318
00:16:57.850 --> 00:16:59.552
[singing continues]

319
00:16:59.652 --> 00:17:03.190
Could've been a SEAL. too.
The corps suited me better.

320
00:17:03.990 --> 00:17:06.426
I'm more blunt force weapon
than scalpel.

321
00:17:08.695 --> 00:17:11.398
Place is a sniper's dream.
Eyes peeled.

322
00:17:11.531 --> 00:17:14.901
[Clarkson] This mine will
help us bridge the gap

323
00:17:15.001 --> 00:17:18.271
with our competitors.
making us safer.

324
00:17:18.371 --> 00:17:21.074
richer and less dependent...

325
00:17:21.174 --> 00:17:24.043
[overlapping shouting]

326
00:17:24.177 --> 00:17:26.045
♪ tense music ♪

327
00:17:33.720 --> 00:17:34.887
I got eyes on
a possible triggerman.

328
00:17:34.987 --> 00:17:36.054
<i>Say again. possible triggerman.</i>

329
00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:37.924
Black bag. in front of the dais.

330
00:17:38.057 --> 00:17:39.426
[Calvin]
Avalanche. Avalanche. Avalanche.

331
00:17:39.526 --> 00:17:40.427
Madam. I need you down now.
I need you down--

332
00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:42.962
[high-pitched ringing]

333
00:17:45.064 --> 00:17:46.433
[screaming]

334
00:17:46.733 --> 00:17:48.901
♪

335
00:17:52.339 --> 00:17:53.606
Is he conscious?

336
00:17:53.706 --> 00:17:54.907
Check him up top for blood.

337
00:17:55.007 --> 00:17:56.576
- [groans]
- Come on. stay with me.

338
00:18:02.249 --> 00:18:04.484
♪ dramatic music ♪

339
00:18:08.755 --> 00:18:11.057
Is Rainwater gonna be okay?

340
00:18:13.126 --> 00:18:15.395
I need to help Cal
find whoever did this.

341
00:18:15.495 --> 00:18:17.930
<i>Let's get you home safe. first.</i>

342
00:18:24.704 --> 00:18:25.838
[Harry]
<i>Avoided disaster today.</i>

343
00:18:25.938 --> 00:18:27.874
thanks to
my team's quick thinking.

344
00:18:27.974 --> 00:18:29.642
What's the Broken Rock
chairman's status?

345
00:18:29.776 --> 00:18:30.743
[Calvin]
He has a fighting chance.

346
00:18:30.843 --> 00:18:32.212
thanks to some Navy medicine.

347
00:18:32.312 --> 00:18:34.013
Secretary is already
wheels up for D.C.

348
00:18:34.113 --> 00:18:35.448
[Owen]
Marshals have lead.

349
00:18:35.582 --> 00:18:37.284
but let's keep
the communication lines open.

350
00:18:37.384 --> 00:18:39.118
Mm-hmm.

351
00:18:40.453 --> 00:18:43.289
White House is
gonna clean my plow.

352
00:18:43.290 --> 00:18:44.657
we don't track down this bomber.

353
00:18:44.757 --> 00:18:46.293
Lack of leads is frustrating.

354
00:18:46.393 --> 00:18:48.160
[Andrea] We're in the sticks.
not Times Square. okay?

355
00:18:48.161 --> 00:18:50.397
There's no surveillance. no
manpower to question witnesses

356
00:18:50.497 --> 00:18:51.831
or identify suspects.

357
00:18:51.931 --> 00:18:54.000
Time to sink or swim. frogman.

358
00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:56.135
Get me that bomber.

359
00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:02.309
Please tell me
you have something.

360
00:19:03.075 --> 00:19:05.678
Strands from the backpack
covered in explosive residue.

361
00:19:05.812 --> 00:19:06.946
Pressure cooker lid.

362
00:19:07.046 --> 00:19:08.648
We're looking at
a homemade bomb.

363
00:19:08.748 --> 00:19:11.150
By whom? This a lone wolf

364
00:19:11.284 --> 00:19:12.519
or part of a. you know.
larger conspiracy?

365
00:19:12.652 --> 00:19:13.620
[Andrea]
Did cowboy give you

366
00:19:13.720 --> 00:19:14.987
a description on the triggerman?

367
00:19:15.087 --> 00:19:16.856
Nah. he was too far
for anything useful.

368
00:19:16.956 --> 00:19:18.157
Okay. Belle. use your contacts

369
00:19:18.291 --> 00:19:20.427
at ATF. you start
digging into that bomb.

370
00:19:20.527 --> 00:19:22.462
Miles. I want you running point
on collecting video footage.

371
00:19:22.562 --> 00:19:23.663
We're talking local news.

372
00:19:23.796 --> 00:19:25.064
social media.
You know what to do.

373
00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:26.199
Best witnesses were
near the blast.

374
00:19:26.333 --> 00:19:27.834
I'll canvass Bozeman General.

375
00:19:27.934 --> 00:19:29.836
Think your Bronx charm is
gonna get people to open up?

376
00:19:29.969 --> 00:19:31.638
[Calvin]
Kayce really wants to help.

377
00:19:31.738 --> 00:19:34.206
That blast radius had a lot
of Broken Rock residents in it.

378
00:19:34.207 --> 00:19:36.376
They-they will
talk to him. okay.

379
00:19:36.476 --> 00:19:37.877
Let's go manhunting. Come on.

380
00:19:38.010 --> 00:19:39.679
[siren whoops]

381
00:19:41.113 --> 00:19:42.849
Thank you.

382
00:19:44.351 --> 00:19:46.018
[Andrea]
How's it work around here?

383
00:19:46.118 --> 00:19:47.387
Rez folks trust you

384
00:19:47.487 --> 00:19:48.521
since you gave them land
the size of Rhode Island?

385
00:19:49.922 --> 00:19:52.024
My wife is Broken Rock.

386
00:19:52.124 --> 00:19:54.026
Raised our son there
for a while.

387
00:20:00.500 --> 00:20:04.704
Sun rarely shines on the rez.

388
00:20:04.837 --> 00:20:06.205
but this

389
00:20:06.306 --> 00:20:08.741
is one of our darkest days.

390
00:20:08.841 --> 00:20:11.411
- How's Rainwater?
- Still in surgery.

391
00:20:12.645 --> 00:20:14.080
He's a fighter.

392
00:20:17.650 --> 00:20:20.119
Picked a hell of a day
to leave the ranch.

393
00:20:21.688 --> 00:20:24.457
Violence has a way
of finding the Duttons.

394
00:20:30.330 --> 00:20:31.763
[Belle]
<i>Explosive powder used</i>

395
00:20:31.764 --> 00:20:34.267
tracks to
Montana Department of Energy.

396
00:20:34.367 --> 00:20:35.734
Can you pinpoint
where it's from?

397
00:20:35.735 --> 00:20:37.370
Any one
of hundreds of job sites.

398
00:20:37.470 --> 00:20:39.472
But I was able
to track the serial number

399
00:20:39.572 --> 00:20:41.441
used on
the pressure cooker lid to

400
00:20:41.574 --> 00:20:43.510
a Buckners's Hardware
near Broken Rock.

401
00:20:43.610 --> 00:20:45.445
Near Broken Rock?

402
00:20:45.545 --> 00:20:47.380
A locally built bomb
likely means local bomber.

403
00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:49.081
Did you ID the buyer?

404
00:20:49.215 --> 00:20:50.617
Paid in cash.
no security footage.

405
00:20:50.717 --> 00:20:52.117
Well. I'd say that's

406
00:20:52.118 --> 00:20:53.586
a nail in
the reservation's coffin.

407
00:20:53.686 --> 00:20:54.821
You have means. motive.

408
00:20:54.921 --> 00:20:56.456
- opportunity.
- Maybe get some evidence

409
00:20:56.556 --> 00:20:57.924
before you go starting
the next Wounded Knee.

410
00:20:58.024 --> 00:20:59.359
[Calvin]
Look. investigation goes

411
00:20:59.459 --> 00:21:00.927
where the clues lead us. Miles.

412
00:21:01.027 --> 00:21:02.729
Check this out.

413
00:21:04.096 --> 00:21:06.032
Man in the hat
wearing the backpack.

414
00:21:06.132 --> 00:21:07.800
moving through the crowd.

415
00:21:07.900 --> 00:21:09.135
Disappears near the blast zone.

416
00:21:09.268 --> 00:21:10.637
Do you have him
dropping the bag. though?

417
00:21:11.438 --> 00:21:13.340
There's nothing
at the barrier yet.

418
00:21:13.440 --> 00:21:16.274
and the explosion's
less than a minute later.

419
00:21:16.275 --> 00:21:17.910
Facial recognition get a hit?

420
00:21:24.250 --> 00:21:26.952
[tech] It's Jim Kane.
member of Broken Rock.

421
00:21:26.953 --> 00:21:28.455
He's married with a daughter.

422
00:21:28.555 --> 00:21:30.056
Works at a state-run oil rig.

423
00:21:30.156 --> 00:21:32.291
Gives him access to explosives.

424
00:21:34.126 --> 00:21:36.295
His brother
died of cancer last year.

425
00:21:36.396 --> 00:21:38.498
likely caused
by toxins on the rez.

426
00:21:38.631 --> 00:21:40.467
Could be motive.

427
00:21:42.301 --> 00:21:44.671
Jim's tough. but a family man.

428
00:21:44.771 --> 00:21:46.673
Whatever he is.
the bomb went off way too soon

429
00:21:46.806 --> 00:21:48.140
for him to be the triggerman.

430
00:21:48.240 --> 00:21:50.176
Explosion was right after
the bag was placed.

431
00:21:51.310 --> 00:21:52.679
Good chance he was fragged.

432
00:21:52.812 --> 00:21:54.514
Hey.

433
00:21:54.647 --> 00:21:55.748
- Excuse me.
- Yeah.

434
00:21:55.848 --> 00:21:57.148
Have you seen this man?

435
00:21:57.149 --> 00:21:59.986
Uh. looks like
a John Doe we triaged.

436
00:22:00.086 --> 00:22:01.721
He's in recovery.

437
00:22:01.821 --> 00:22:03.189
[Andrea]
Jim Kane?

438
00:22:03.289 --> 00:22:04.957
Deputy U.S. Marshal Andrea Cruz.

439
00:22:05.057 --> 00:22:07.794
You're a person of interest
in today's bombing.

440
00:22:08.628 --> 00:22:10.430
I'll tell Cal we have Kane.

441
00:22:12.865 --> 00:22:15.402
Oh. Sorry.
I didn't know he had company.

442
00:22:19.105 --> 00:22:20.373
[buttons beep on monitor]

443
00:22:21.908 --> 00:22:25.111
♪ suspenseful music ♪

444
00:22:42.695 --> 00:22:44.864
♪

445
00:23:05.384 --> 00:23:07.554
♪

446
00:23:23.603 --> 00:23:25.905
[grunting]

447
00:23:32.111 --> 00:23:34.747
♪

448
00:23:55.301 --> 00:23:57.504
[panting]

449
00:24:03.976 --> 00:24:05.244
[Belle]
<i>John Decker. 40.</i>

450
00:24:05.344 --> 00:24:07.679
Army vet.
10th Mountain Division.

451
00:24:07.680 --> 00:24:08.981
currently resides up north

452
00:24:09.115 --> 00:24:10.550
- in Conrad.
- [Calvin] 10th Mountain's gonna

453
00:24:10.650 --> 00:24:12.418
give him explosives training.
Okay. what's his

454
00:24:12.519 --> 00:24:14.687
- connection to Kane?
- Worked together last year.

455
00:24:14.821 --> 00:24:16.321
same oil rig.

456
00:24:16.322 --> 00:24:18.825
So old work buddies reunited
to take out the secretary?

457
00:24:18.925 --> 00:24:21.260
Yeah. well. Kane had
access to the explosives.

458
00:24:21.360 --> 00:24:23.029
Decker knew how
to make the bomb. and...

459
00:24:23.162 --> 00:24:25.031
sounds like a conspiracy to me.

460
00:24:25.131 --> 00:24:27.867
[Andrea] I turn my back on you
for two seconds.

461
00:24:28.701 --> 00:24:30.436
How's the arm?

462
00:24:30.537 --> 00:24:31.703
I've had worse.

463
00:24:31.704 --> 00:24:33.906
So. who's the dead guy?

464
00:24:34.006 --> 00:24:35.174
Former coworker of Kane's.

465
00:24:35.274 --> 00:24:36.408
It seems
they were in this together.

466
00:24:36.509 --> 00:24:37.543
[Kayce]
Does anything prove that?

467
00:24:37.544 --> 00:24:39.045
I looked into Kane's eyes.

468
00:24:39.145 --> 00:24:41.147
That... that man's not a killer.

469
00:24:41.247 --> 00:24:42.348
Dead guy's phone has nothing.

470
00:24:42.481 --> 00:24:44.049
- He was disciplined.
- Thank you.

471
00:24:44.050 --> 00:24:45.752
Except for the part
where he tried to kill you.

472
00:24:45.852 --> 00:24:48.087
What's this video game app?

473
00:24:49.121 --> 00:24:50.557
[nurse]
Coming through.

474
00:24:53.025 --> 00:24:54.694
One second. fellas.

475
00:24:57.697 --> 00:24:59.031
During the war on terror.

476
00:24:59.131 --> 00:25:00.967
the enemy used
game chatrooms to communicate.

477
00:25:01.868 --> 00:25:03.435
[whimpering]

478
00:25:04.537 --> 00:25:05.738
Hey.

479
00:25:07.707 --> 00:25:08.941
Know them?

480
00:25:10.543 --> 00:25:12.879
Jim Kane's wife and daughter.

481
00:25:12.979 --> 00:25:14.581
You want
to explain why a dead man

482
00:25:14.681 --> 00:25:16.214
has your wife and kid
on his phone?

483
00:25:16.215 --> 00:25:17.383
[wife whimpering]

484
00:25:17.516 --> 00:25:19.118
Were you leveraged
into the bombing?

485
00:25:21.754 --> 00:25:23.756
Is your family in danger?

486
00:25:26.926 --> 00:25:30.730
There's no greater violation
than having your child taken.

487
00:25:31.564 --> 00:25:33.565
I've lived that horror.

488
00:25:33.566 --> 00:25:38.404
so I know that sometimes
good men have to do bad things.

489
00:25:40.439 --> 00:25:41.741
I'll crawl through hell

490
00:25:41.841 --> 00:25:43.242
to find your family.
but I need your help.

491
00:25:43.342 --> 00:25:45.243
[Mo]
Jim. I trust Kayce

492
00:25:45.244 --> 00:25:47.714
with the lives of
the people I love.

493
00:25:47.814 --> 00:25:49.582
You should. too.

494
00:25:56.623 --> 00:25:58.725
They were gonna kill my family.

495
00:25:59.892 --> 00:26:02.194
I didn't want to hurt anyone.

496
00:26:03.763 --> 00:26:05.264
- I...
- [Andrea] Where are your wife

497
00:26:05.364 --> 00:26:07.033
and daughter being held?

498
00:26:08.901 --> 00:26:09.902
I don't know.

499
00:26:10.002 --> 00:26:11.771
We were apart.

500
00:26:11.871 --> 00:26:14.140
You got to get
Tiva and Lucy back.

501
00:26:14.240 --> 00:26:15.775
I can't face
this world without 'em.

502
00:26:15.908 --> 00:26:18.144
[Andrea] Who else was
Decker working with?

503
00:26:18.244 --> 00:26:19.779
[Jim]
I was only with him.

504
00:26:19.912 --> 00:26:21.681
They used those videos
to keep me in line.

505
00:26:21.781 --> 00:26:23.950
Did he say why
he was targeting the secretary?

506
00:26:24.083 --> 00:26:25.151
The secretary?

507
00:26:25.251 --> 00:26:27.453
Decker wanted Rainwater dead.

508
00:26:31.891 --> 00:26:33.292
So the secretary
wasn't the target.

509
00:26:33.425 --> 00:26:35.461
the Broken Rock chief was?

510
00:26:36.295 --> 00:26:37.697
Broken Rock chairman.

511
00:26:37.797 --> 00:26:38.998
Tough spot for Kane.

512
00:26:39.098 --> 00:26:41.132
Kill Rainwater
or your family dies.

513
00:26:41.133 --> 00:26:42.467
[tech 2]
Social media links

514
00:26:42.468 --> 00:26:44.203
Decker to a survivalist group.

515
00:26:44.303 --> 00:26:45.337
the Trail Keepers.

516
00:26:45.471 --> 00:26:47.807
Anti-government. anti-globalism

517
00:26:47.907 --> 00:26:49.508
- and anti-land back movement.
- Rainwater's campaign

518
00:26:49.642 --> 00:26:51.911
to recover our land
put him in the crosshairs.

519
00:26:52.011 --> 00:26:54.380
But why go through the trouble
of making Kane a patsy

520
00:26:54.480 --> 00:26:56.615
and the chairman seem like
collateral damage?

521
00:26:56.716 --> 00:26:58.317
[Miles]
Because "angry Native killer"

522
00:26:58.450 --> 00:27:00.186
wouldn't raise
as many questions.

523
00:27:00.319 --> 00:27:02.154
especially from law enforcement.

524
00:27:02.254 --> 00:27:03.890
Guilty as charged.
Deputy Marshal.

525
00:27:03.990 --> 00:27:06.191
Okay. so. the Trail Keepers
are gonna be our best lead.

526
00:27:06.192 --> 00:27:07.659
- Where do they camp?
- I'm working on it.

527
00:27:07.660 --> 00:27:09.028
- Okay. thank you.
- [Miles] Instead of tracking

528
00:27:09.128 --> 00:27:10.495
the militia.
maybe I can track Tiva.

529
00:27:10.496 --> 00:27:11.931
Lots of parents have
started putting trackers

530
00:27:12.031 --> 00:27:13.032
on their kids since
so many go missing.

531
00:27:13.165 --> 00:27:14.365
Kane never mentioned anything

532
00:27:14.366 --> 00:27:15.735
to Andrea or Kayce
about a tracker.

533
00:27:15.835 --> 00:27:17.168
[Belle] Come on.
Your wife tell you all the ways

534
00:27:17.169 --> 00:27:18.503
she tried to
keep your daughter safe?

535
00:27:18.504 --> 00:27:20.707
Only when she left
with her for good.

536
00:27:20.840 --> 00:27:22.341
Look. Dust Cloud.
get on the trackers.

537
00:27:22.474 --> 00:27:23.875
okay? 'Cause at some point.

538
00:27:23.876 --> 00:27:25.344
these Trail Keepers.
they're gonna realize

539
00:27:25.477 --> 00:27:27.246
Decker's not coming back
and we're in their playbook.

540
00:27:28.147 --> 00:27:30.082
Deputy Marshal Calvin. a word?

541
00:27:39.892 --> 00:27:41.693
You want to tell me
why there's a Dutton

542
00:27:41.694 --> 00:27:43.362
dropping bodies for this unit?

543
00:27:43.462 --> 00:27:45.597
Kayce's my former teammate.
one man force-multiplier.

544
00:27:45.698 --> 00:27:47.867
You couldn't find
one of them Menendez brothers

545
00:27:47.967 --> 00:27:49.468
or some kin of El Chapo instead?

546
00:27:49.568 --> 00:27:51.704
He's a war hero.
What's the issue?

547
00:27:51.804 --> 00:27:53.239
The issue is
we Marshals uphold the law.

548
00:27:53.372 --> 00:27:54.874
the Duttons bend it.

549
00:27:57.476 --> 00:27:59.511
Is there something
between you and Kayce's family

550
00:27:59.611 --> 00:28:00.713
that I should know about?

551
00:28:00.847 --> 00:28:02.348
Just 40 years
of personal history.

552
00:28:02.448 --> 00:28:05.284
Duttons are born with
dysfunction in their blood.

553
00:28:07.619 --> 00:28:10.589
Kayce's my brother. so...

554
00:28:10.689 --> 00:28:13.392
you want him out of here.
you do it yourself.

555
00:28:15.294 --> 00:28:16.562
[door opens]

556
00:28:16.695 --> 00:28:18.664
[phone buzzing]

557
00:28:18.765 --> 00:28:20.499
[Calvin]
You weren't kidding about

558
00:28:20.599 --> 00:28:22.600
your whole life
being kill or be killed.

559
00:28:22.601 --> 00:28:24.303
Look. we threw you
into the fire today.

560
00:28:24.403 --> 00:28:26.272
so there's no shame
if you need to stand down.

561
00:28:26.405 --> 00:28:28.374
Told Kane I'd see it through.

562
00:28:28.474 --> 00:28:29.441
[Miles]
Got it.

563
00:28:29.575 --> 00:28:30.576
Tiva has a tracker.

564
00:28:30.676 --> 00:28:32.044
It's pinging in Glacier Park.

565
00:28:32.144 --> 00:28:33.512
Okay. Andrea. you're
gonna quarterback from here

566
00:28:33.612 --> 00:28:35.080
just in case anything
pops off locally.

567
00:28:35.081 --> 00:28:36.614
The rest of you...
[clicks tongue] ...on me.

568
00:28:36.615 --> 00:28:38.150
Target's at least
a few hundred miles away.

569
00:28:38.250 --> 00:28:39.418
How we gonna close the gap?

570
00:28:39.518 --> 00:28:41.153
Not on horseback.

571
00:28:41.253 --> 00:28:44.423
♪ dramatic music ♪

572
00:28:46.425 --> 00:28:48.094
Might not want
to high port that rifle

573
00:28:48.194 --> 00:28:50.129
with our rotor above us.

574
00:28:53.299 --> 00:28:54.566
Okay.

575
00:28:54.666 --> 00:28:57.203
Back on the crazy train.

576
00:29:00.572 --> 00:29:02.440
Only law enforcement
near the Trail Keepers

577
00:29:02.441 --> 00:29:04.143
is one of Kilborn's
game wardens.

578
00:29:04.276 --> 00:29:05.778
30 miles away.

579
00:29:05.912 --> 00:29:08.613
How did Decker know
to grab Kane's family three days

580
00:29:08.614 --> 00:29:10.749
before the secretary's
trip was made public?

581
00:29:11.550 --> 00:29:13.285
The Trail Keepers
got inside information

582
00:29:13.419 --> 00:29:14.620
from someone. Good catch.

583
00:29:14.720 --> 00:29:15.788
All right. dig into who had

584
00:29:15.922 --> 00:29:17.256
advance word
of the secretary's trip.

585
00:29:17.356 --> 00:29:18.457
Cross-reference everyone

586
00:29:18.590 --> 00:29:19.959
with Decker
and the Trail Keepers.

587
00:29:20.226 --> 00:29:21.727
♪

588
00:29:21.828 --> 00:29:22.794
[Miles]
It's quiet.

589
00:29:22.795 --> 00:29:24.063
Maybe they bailed.

590
00:29:24.163 --> 00:29:26.497
Tracker's still pinging
on the inside.

591
00:29:26.498 --> 00:29:27.967
[Belle]
Should we do a callout?

592
00:29:28.968 --> 00:29:31.303
No. we got
the element of surprise.

593
00:29:31.403 --> 00:29:34.173
Slow is smooth
and smooth is fast. Let's go.

594
00:29:36.843 --> 00:29:38.044
Found a link to Decker.

595
00:29:38.144 --> 00:29:39.645
His Army commanding officer

596
00:29:39.745 --> 00:29:43.515
is the Fish. Game and Parks
Director. Owen Kilborn.

597
00:29:44.350 --> 00:29:45.852
I just told him
the target we're hitting.

598
00:29:45.952 --> 00:29:47.653
- [Andrea] <i>One. this is Knife.</i>
- Take cover!

599
00:29:47.753 --> 00:29:49.655
<i>Abort. Say again. abort.</i>

600
00:29:53.625 --> 00:29:55.427
Lucy and Tiva don't
got time for this.

601
00:29:55.527 --> 00:29:56.863
Getting shot up out here.

602
00:29:56.963 --> 00:29:58.330
I'm gonna go right.
draw 'em out.

603
00:29:58.430 --> 00:29:59.731
Okay. move. move!

604
00:29:59.832 --> 00:30:01.700
♪ tense music ♪

605
00:30:13.379 --> 00:30:15.314
I'm moving on target.

606
00:30:19.986 --> 00:30:21.153
Kayce.

607
00:30:21.253 --> 00:30:23.389
<i>we're gonna make
entry in three seconds.</i>

608
00:30:30.062 --> 00:30:32.231
♪

609
00:30:34.566 --> 00:30:36.168
[man groaning]

610
00:30:37.436 --> 00:30:39.205
[man groans]

611
00:30:39.705 --> 00:30:41.207
[handcuffs clicking]

612
00:30:44.576 --> 00:30:45.711
Ah!

613
00:30:48.080 --> 00:30:50.249
♪

614
00:30:56.588 --> 00:30:58.190
Clear.

615
00:31:05.097 --> 00:31:06.732
- [gunshot]
- [grunts]

616
00:31:11.170 --> 00:31:12.571
[breathing heavily]

617
00:31:12.704 --> 00:31:14.106
[Belle coughing]

618
00:31:15.374 --> 00:31:17.676
Got your strike plate.
You're good. You're good.

619
00:31:18.844 --> 00:31:21.047
♪

620
00:31:22.514 --> 00:31:24.416
[crying softly]

621
00:31:24.516 --> 00:31:26.252
[Calvin]
No sign of the girl.

622
00:31:26.385 --> 00:31:28.419
[Kayce] Probably using
the girl as a shield.

623
00:31:28.420 --> 00:31:30.456
Hey. hey. listen.
We're U.S. Marshals. okay?

624
00:31:30.589 --> 00:31:32.391
We're here to help you.

625
00:31:34.193 --> 00:31:36.594
Here's the tracker.

626
00:31:36.595 --> 00:31:37.763
They lured us in.

627
00:31:37.863 --> 00:31:39.932
[crying]
My-my baby. they took her.

628
00:31:40.732 --> 00:31:41.767
[Calvin] Do you know
where they're headed?

629
00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:43.002
[Lucy]
No.

630
00:31:43.769 --> 00:31:45.804
They-they can't have gone far.

631
00:31:45.904 --> 00:31:47.073
Please.

632
00:31:49.641 --> 00:31:51.343
Where are they taking the girl?

633
00:31:52.511 --> 00:31:54.645
[grunting]

634
00:31:54.646 --> 00:31:56.348
Detailed op like this
has an exfil plan.

635
00:31:56.448 --> 00:31:58.917
- What is it?
- I don't know.

636
00:31:59.018 --> 00:32:00.486
[screaming]

637
00:32:01.753 --> 00:32:03.122
I have a lot more ways
of hurting you

638
00:32:03.222 --> 00:32:05.124
than you have of resisting me.

639
00:32:06.392 --> 00:32:07.793
[groaning]

640
00:32:07.926 --> 00:32:09.328
Cracker Lake.

641
00:32:09.461 --> 00:32:11.263
Kilborn and the other guy
are taking her there.

642
00:32:11.363 --> 00:32:12.630
Hey.

643
00:32:12.631 --> 00:32:14.266
Marshal badge means
we got to fight clean.

644
00:32:14.366 --> 00:32:15.968
You can fight clean.

645
00:32:16.068 --> 00:32:17.536
I'll fight to win.

646
00:32:25.011 --> 00:32:26.979
♪ suspenseful music ♪

647
00:32:48.934 --> 00:32:51.503
- [Owen] Come on. kid!
- [Tiva] Leave me alone.

648
00:32:51.603 --> 00:32:53.505
No. no!

649
00:32:53.605 --> 00:32:55.007
[militia]
Hey!

650
00:32:56.875 --> 00:32:58.010
[Calvin]
Okay. let her go. Kilborn.

651
00:32:58.110 --> 00:33:00.046
Drop it! Or she's dead.

652
00:33:03.182 --> 00:33:05.484
- [Calvin] Just take it easy.
- Drop it!

653
00:33:07.053 --> 00:33:08.854
[Calvin]
Hey. let's talk this over.

654
00:33:11.657 --> 00:33:12.691
- [gunshot]
- [Tiva yelps]

655
00:33:12.791 --> 00:33:14.026
[body thumps]

656
00:33:15.827 --> 00:33:18.897
- ♪ gentle music
- [Kilborn grunts]

657
00:33:20.366 --> 00:33:24.270
You've... stopped... nothing.

658
00:33:33.379 --> 00:33:35.547
It's okay. all right?
You're okay now.

659
00:33:35.647 --> 00:33:37.215
You're okay.

660
00:33:37.216 --> 00:33:38.917
Come on. You're okay. Come on.

661
00:33:39.718 --> 00:33:41.853
♪

662
00:33:42.654 --> 00:33:45.256
Uh. is that some sort of
native healing balm?

663
00:33:45.257 --> 00:33:47.559
I'm rather particular about
what I put on my body.

664
00:33:47.659 --> 00:33:49.060
Passed down from the elders.

665
00:33:49.061 --> 00:33:51.229
My grandmother used it on me.
her grandmother

666
00:33:51.230 --> 00:33:52.230
on her.

667
00:33:52.231 --> 00:33:54.866
Vaseline. [laughs]

668
00:33:54.966 --> 00:33:56.368
[Andrea]
Hey.

669
00:33:56.468 --> 00:33:58.837
glad you came home with
a full headcount today.

670
00:34:01.140 --> 00:34:03.142
You kept your promise to Kane.

671
00:34:03.242 --> 00:34:05.077
My word's about all I have left.

672
00:34:05.177 --> 00:34:06.345
[Miles]
More than Kilborn can say.

673
00:34:06.445 --> 00:34:07.746
Morally bankrupt traitor.

674
00:34:07.879 --> 00:34:09.648
Though not financially.

675
00:34:09.748 --> 00:34:12.618
I discovered he had $250.000

676
00:34:12.718 --> 00:34:14.486
wired to him
from an offshore account.

677
00:34:14.586 --> 00:34:16.455
Bombing was a mercenary job.

678
00:34:16.555 --> 00:34:17.889
Would've been an easy payday

679
00:34:17.989 --> 00:34:19.525
if Kane had died in the blast.

680
00:34:20.726 --> 00:34:21.960
Let's take the win. y'all.

681
00:34:22.094 --> 00:34:25.231
My modern day posse
came up big today.

682
00:34:30.569 --> 00:34:32.971
[Noah James' "Set Free" playing]

683
00:34:42.047 --> 00:34:44.483
[sighs]

684
00:34:44.583 --> 00:34:45.884
Does it get easier?

685
00:34:45.984 --> 00:34:47.753
What's that?

686
00:34:47.853 --> 00:34:49.288
The killing.

687
00:34:49.388 --> 00:34:51.890
I was kicked out of the Corps
before I was deployed.

688
00:34:52.791 --> 00:34:54.626
<i>♪ That I've had since... ♪</i>

689
00:34:54.760 --> 00:34:55.894
Hmm.

690
00:34:57.329 --> 00:34:58.797
No.

691
00:35:00.065 --> 00:35:02.268
'Cause it's the one thing
in life you can't undo.

692
00:35:02.368 --> 00:35:05.904
<i>♪ ...every night of every week ♪</i>

693
00:35:06.004 --> 00:35:09.807
<i>♪ He said. "Boy.
if you want to be something ♪</i>

694
00:35:09.808 --> 00:35:12.544
<i>♪ You can't do it without me" ♪</i>

695
00:35:14.846 --> 00:35:17.148
<i>♪ I won't let no devil ♪</i>

696
00:35:17.149 --> 00:35:21.652
<i>♪ Have a hold on me ♪</i>

697
00:35:21.653 --> 00:35:23.189
<i>♪ It's like a bull... ♪</i>

698
00:35:23.322 --> 00:35:24.990
- [Andrea] Oh!
- [foosball table rattles]

699
00:35:25.090 --> 00:35:26.825
[Miles]
Want a drink?

700
00:35:26.958 --> 00:35:28.327
Come on. drink.

701
00:35:28.460 --> 00:35:30.729
- [Taser crackles]
- [Miles groans]

702
00:35:32.030 --> 00:35:34.233
- [Miles] Show us what you got.
- Uh. Isabel Turek.

703
00:35:34.333 --> 00:35:36.502
right? Family bred
cutting horses.

704
00:35:36.602 --> 00:35:40.105
Ah. appreciate that's what
you remember them from.

705
00:35:42.708 --> 00:35:45.311
Look. team knows me as Skinner.

706
00:35:46.111 --> 00:35:47.679
I'd like to keep it that way.

707
00:35:47.813 --> 00:35:49.315
Sure.

708
00:35:49.415 --> 00:35:51.983
Yeah. family secrets
are an old pastime.

709
00:35:55.354 --> 00:35:57.489
- [Miles] That's on you.
- Excuse me.

710
00:35:57.589 --> 00:35:59.691
I need to go stick a cork

711
00:35:59.825 --> 00:36:01.092
in these two.

712
00:36:01.193 --> 00:36:03.028
- [shouts]
- [laughs]

713
00:36:04.563 --> 00:36:07.233
[overlapping chatter]

714
00:36:07.366 --> 00:36:09.167
[laughter]

715
00:36:11.337 --> 00:36:13.205
You realize
this is the antidote.

716
00:36:13.339 --> 00:36:16.575
- For what?
- All the violence we've endured

717
00:36:16.708 --> 00:36:18.810
and inflicted.

718
00:36:18.910 --> 00:36:21.912
But helping others.
finding new purpose.

719
00:36:21.913 --> 00:36:24.716
being a part
of the pack again. that's...

720
00:36:24.816 --> 00:36:27.052
that's how you
wash the stains of war away.

721
00:36:27.152 --> 00:36:29.488
Some stains are permanent.

722
00:36:32.358 --> 00:36:34.226
Eh.

723
00:36:34.326 --> 00:36:36.094
We owe it
to the people that we lost

724
00:36:36.228 --> 00:36:38.964
to make our lives
mean something. so...

725
00:36:39.965 --> 00:36:42.901
But what we did today mattered.

726
00:36:43.669 --> 00:36:46.071
♪ introspective music

727
00:36:46.171 --> 00:36:47.906
[Calvin]
Okay. let's go.

728
00:36:49.107 --> 00:36:50.576
[Belle]
Hey. Hey. hey. hey.

729
00:36:50.676 --> 00:36:53.312
[overlapping chatter]

730
00:36:56.682 --> 00:36:58.717
♪

731
00:36:59.485 --> 00:37:02.220
Here I was.
assuming my issues went away

732
00:37:02.321 --> 00:37:03.789
with the Dutton Ranch.

733
00:37:03.889 --> 00:37:05.757
I sense that extends

734
00:37:05.857 --> 00:37:07.526
to East Camp.

735
00:37:08.294 --> 00:37:11.162
You know. I was choosing
the best path for my family.

736
00:37:12.631 --> 00:37:15.934
No matter where I go. I end up
on the wrong side of the fence.

737
00:37:17.303 --> 00:37:19.137
Well. if you don't
like the path you're on.

738
00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:21.440
you have the power
to change course.

739
00:37:22.841 --> 00:37:25.010
[Mo] Did a lot of good
with the marshals.

740
00:37:25.110 --> 00:37:27.446
And gave the Kane family
<i>piya wiconi.</i>

741
00:37:27.579 --> 00:37:29.647
<i>Piya wiconi?</i>

742
00:37:29.648 --> 00:37:31.450
[Thomas]
New beginning.

743
00:37:31.550 --> 00:37:33.552
They are possible.

744
00:37:35.621 --> 00:37:39.624
It was nice to kill for
someone rather than...

745
00:37:39.625 --> 00:37:41.159
something.

746
00:37:42.093 --> 00:37:45.130
Duttons are all born
with the killer instinct.

747
00:37:46.532 --> 00:37:48.466
But you're not a killer. Kayce.

748
00:37:48.467 --> 00:37:50.436
You're a protector.

749
00:37:52.037 --> 00:37:54.406
All the wolves out there.

750
00:37:54.506 --> 00:37:56.975
we need sheepdogs
more than ever. Kayce.

751
00:37:57.108 --> 00:37:59.378
♪ introspective music ♪

752
00:38:03.982 --> 00:38:06.852
[birds singing]

753
00:38:19.865 --> 00:38:20.866
Where you going?

754
00:38:20.999 --> 00:38:22.300
Got to get the herd out.

755
00:38:22.401 --> 00:38:24.135
Herd can wait.

756
00:38:25.671 --> 00:38:27.172
Come sit.

757
00:38:28.840 --> 00:38:30.008
[exhales]

758
00:38:37.015 --> 00:38:39.350
Sorry for disobeying you
at the rally.

759
00:38:39.351 --> 00:38:42.253
Don't you ever apologize
for standing up for your mother.

760
00:38:44.322 --> 00:38:46.758
I'm the one
who should apologize.

761
00:38:49.027 --> 00:38:50.362
I fought so hard to get out

762
00:38:50.462 --> 00:38:51.730
from under the weight
of the Yellowstone.

763
00:38:51.830 --> 00:38:53.198
and here I am.
forcing you to live

764
00:38:53.298 --> 00:38:54.966
like my family's lived
for a hundred years.

765
00:38:58.537 --> 00:39:01.139
But everything changed
when Mom died.

766
00:39:02.574 --> 00:39:04.109
Yeah.

767
00:39:07.345 --> 00:39:09.347
The only thing
more cruel than losing a parent

768
00:39:09.448 --> 00:39:11.416
is losing the wrong one.

769
00:39:11.417 --> 00:39:13.585
♪ gentle music ♪

770
00:39:14.586 --> 00:39:16.888
The only reason I'm gripping
this place so tight

771
00:39:16.988 --> 00:39:19.925
is 'cause it's the only thing
I have to offer you. son.

772
00:39:20.726 --> 00:39:22.761
But what if
I'm not sure I want it?

773
00:39:24.763 --> 00:39:26.097
What's so funny?

774
00:39:27.065 --> 00:39:29.768
Your grandfather.
he warned me about this.

775
00:39:29.868 --> 00:39:32.604
He said one day you'd test me.

776
00:39:34.105 --> 00:39:36.775
Force me to make a decision that
not only affects your future.

777
00:39:36.908 --> 00:39:38.510
but my place in it.

778
00:39:39.244 --> 00:39:42.448
I want you
to forge your own path.

779
00:39:44.416 --> 00:39:47.519
East Camp is your home.
it's not your destiny.

780
00:39:52.090 --> 00:39:54.325
You won't hate me for that?

781
00:39:56.695 --> 00:39:59.030
I've lost my teammates.

782
00:39:59.130 --> 00:40:01.433
my parents.

783
00:40:01.533 --> 00:40:04.202
my brothers. and even my wife

784
00:40:04.302 --> 00:40:06.438
and I'm still standing.

785
00:40:09.808 --> 00:40:12.343
But ending up
on the wrong side of you?

786
00:40:14.846 --> 00:40:16.247
That'd be the end of me. son.

787
00:40:16.347 --> 00:40:19.451
<i>♪ Every time
that there's a shadow ♪</i>

788
00:40:19.551 --> 00:40:22.554
- <i>♪ Out the corner of my eye ♪</i>
- [door opens]

789
00:40:22.654 --> 00:40:23.955
[door closes]

790
00:40:24.089 --> 00:40:26.291
<i>♪ Every time
that there's a whisper ♪</i>

791
00:40:26.391 --> 00:40:30.028
<i>♪ In the middle of the night ♪</i>

792
00:40:31.096 --> 00:40:33.999
<i>♪ I don't fear the darkness ♪</i>

793
00:40:34.800 --> 00:40:37.068
<i>♪ Like I did before ♪</i>

794
00:40:37.803 --> 00:40:42.040
<i>♪ 'Cause I ain't afraid
of ghosts no more... ♪</i>

795
00:40:42.140 --> 00:40:44.543
I miss you. baby.

796
00:40:46.144 --> 00:40:48.980
Miss my wife...

797
00:40:49.114 --> 00:40:51.049
my best friend.

798
00:40:51.983 --> 00:40:54.152
My only friend.

799
00:40:57.689 --> 00:40:59.725
Been so lost.

800
00:41:01.627 --> 00:41:03.662
The best part of me
died with you.

801
00:41:08.634 --> 00:41:10.301
[crying softly]

802
00:41:14.072 --> 00:41:16.675
You always told me
to fight for the life I want.

803
00:41:17.442 --> 00:41:20.145
But I had the life I wanted.
It was with you.

804
00:41:20.245 --> 00:41:22.313
I'm changing paths.

805
00:41:25.617 --> 00:41:28.019
Gonna try to find a new
beginning for me and Tate.

806
00:41:29.187 --> 00:41:31.322
♪

807
00:41:35.026 --> 00:41:37.062
[quietly]
I love you. baby.

808
00:41:47.438 --> 00:41:50.408
<i>♪ It's said that time
will heal ♪</i>

809
00:41:51.176 --> 00:41:54.713
<i>♪ But that clock just
winds and winds ♪</i>

810
00:41:55.446 --> 00:41:58.483
<i>♪ I don't want to wait for you ♪</i>

811
00:41:58.584 --> 00:42:02.753
<i>♪ Till I'm on the other side ♪</i>

812
00:42:02.754 --> 00:42:06.958
<i>♪ I ain't afraid of
ghosts no more ♪</i>

813
00:42:09.060 --> 00:42:13.799
<i>♪ No. I ain't afraid
of ghosts no more ♪</i>

814
00:42:13.899 --> 00:42:15.567
[gunshot]

815
00:42:19.437 --> 00:42:21.740
♪ intense. percussive music ♪

815
